column2: Low Protein Diet - Atlantic Salmon ( Pre-Order Only)
column3:
This Low Protein Diet is only sold in 2 Cup Packs and Pre-Order Only

Support your dog’s health with fresh,  meals designed for dogs who require a low protein diet. These diets balance key nutrients to reduce kidney strain and promote overall wellness.

  • Lower Protein, Phosphorus & Sodium Helps reduce waste buildup and ease kidney workload.

  • Higher Omega-3s Supports kidney function and reduces inflammation.

  • Extra B Vitamins Replenishes nutrients lost through increased urination.

  • Great Taste Encourages eating, even in dogs with low appetite.

  • Hydration Boost High moisture content helps maintain proper hydration.

Ingredients : Salmon, Basmati Rice, Carrots, Cauliflower, Green Beans, Spinach, Blueberries, Pomegranate, Collagen Powder, Ginger, Sunflower Oil, Bone Broth

 

1.2 kcal/g, 264 kcal/cup, 1,166 kcal/kg

column3:
Personalized Nutrition Services

Science-Based Support for a Healthier, Happier Pet

At Waggin Meals Pet Nutrition Co., we offer fully customized meal plans tailored to your dog’s unique needs—backed by science and created with care.

Our Services Include:

Custom Meal Plan Development
Formulated based on your dog’s breed, age, weight, allergies, dietary restrictions, and any medical conditions.

Supplement Recommendations
Personalized guidance on what supplements to add, with trusted sourcing options included.

Meal Prep Instructions
Easy-to-follow prep steps and a list of recommended tools to simplify your routine.

Ongoing Support
Includes two follow-up calls plus unlimited guidance via email to keep your pet on the right track.

Email Resources
You'll receive helpful recipes, feeding tips, and a supplement ordering guide to make implementation seamless.

Canine Nutrition Education
Understand the why behind your pet’s plan—because informed pet parents make empowered choices.

 

Due to hurricane Helene, we are rebuilding and do not offer in person consultations at our main location. However, we do offer and consider this service at your home for an additional fee for Buncombe, Madison, Haywood and Henderson Counties. Contact us for more information.

column3:
Your dog will be pawing for more with these Duck Bars. These are all natural, limited ingredient dog treats made in the USA.  Our Bars are a great  source of protein and full of flavor your dog will love. They are similar in texture to jerky treats and are low in fat.

 Ingredients:

Duck: Duck meat is full of essential nutrients, and it is a great alternative dog food for pets with food allergies to other protein sources like chicken.

Pea Flour: Pea flour is a good source of plant-based protein for dogs. It is also a good source of fiber, which can aid in digestion.

Chickpea: They are a great source of protein, potassium, magnesium, and folate as well as vitamins A, B, and C.

Coconut Glycerin:

Coconut glycerin is a healthy, natural part of animal fats and vegetable oils. Produced from coconut oil, glycerin can potentially increase your dog's lifespan, increase their endurance, improve hydration and help their eyesight.

In fact, it may be the most underappreciated dietary supplement available. 

Already in many of the natural foods we eat, coconut glycerin will not spike blood glucose or insulin—making it perfect for your dog's low carb diet.

Flaxseed: Flaxseed is not only safe for dogs, but it contains several essential nutrients that your dog needs to stay healthy. One of the most common reasons to give your dog flaxseed is to improve their skin and coat health. Flaxseed contains omega fatty acids and is especially high in the omega 6 fatty acid Linoleic Acid.

Ingredients: Duck, pea flour, pea protein, chickpea, coconut glycerin, potato flour, flaxseed,  cane molasses, salt, lactic acid, natural smoke flavor, mixed tocopherols ( a natural source of vitamin E)

Guaranteed Analysis:
Protein (min) 13.0%
Crude Fat (min) 5.0%
Fiber (max) 3.0%
Moisture (max) 25.0%
